descript.abstract: REQUIRED: The outlines of the Historic Districts for the City of South bend as designated by the Historic Perservation Commission of South Bend and St. Joseph County
descript.purpose: REQUIRED: The file was developed from a hard copy map put together by the Historc Perservation Commission.
descript.supplinf: Local Historic Distircts are those areas designated by ordinance as having the historic significance and architectural integrity to comprise a cohesive unit of importnace to the City of South Bend. The Historic Preservation Commission and the District Liasion Committee develop stnadards specifying alterations appropriate to the historic character of the homes and sites within the district. National Register Historic Districts are those areas which, due to national, state, and/or local significance, are listed by the U.S. Department of Interior in the Natinal Register of Historic Places. While not afforded the same protections as a local district, property owners in a National Register disctrict receive the recignition of listing, as well as certain protections from Federally-funded projects and are potentially eligible for investment tax credits and federal grants. Potential Historic Districts indicate neighborhoods where the citizens have expressed an interest in local district designation and which meet the preliminary standards of significance and integrity for consideration by th ehistoric Preservation Commission and the City of South Bend for local district status.
